%% 10 Corpus publish | Host-side immutable release flow
flowchart TB
  subgraph Upload[Normal document upload - separate runtime workflow]
    U1[POST /api/documents]
    U2[Node stores original and MySQL document/job]
    U3[Python parses, embeds and updates Qdrant]
    U4[Callback makes accepted local state READY]
    U1 --> U2 --> U3 --> U4
  end

  U4 -. local state may diverge from current cloud release .-> Local[(Local Corpus state<br/>MySQL + uploads + Qdrant)]

  subgraph DryRun[Read-only publish plan]
    D1[npm run corpus:publish -- --dry-run]
    D2[Read-only MySQL dump, Qdrant scroll and upload stat]
    D3[Validate local eligibility, consistency, paths, secrets and privacy hints]
    D4[Return redacted plan with provisional identity]
    D1 --> D2 --> D3 --> D4
  end
  Local --> D2
  D4 -. no writer stop, snapshot, staging, cloud call or pointer mutation .-> Operator[Operator reviews PII, secrets, rights and scope]

  subgraph Publish[Confirmed immutable publish]
    P1[npm run corpus:publish -- --confirm-reviewed]
    P2{Config and exact confirmation valid?}
    P3[Freeze app and RAG writers]
    P4[Export scoped MySQL without auth tokens]
    P5[Collect exact originals from upload volume]
    P6[Create and download Qdrant collection snapshot]
    P7{Cross-store counts, mapping, checksum, path, secret and privacy checks pass?}
    P8[Build complete manifest and content-v2 identity]
    P8B{Private target can be verified?}
    P9{Release objects already exist?}
    P10[Upload artifacts with create-only precondition]
    P11[Verify existing object metadata and content]
    P12[Upload manifest last]
    P13{Download and verify complete immutable release?}
    P14[Update local current pointer]
    P15[CORPUS_PUBLISH_OK]
    F[Publish fails; previous current pointer remains]
    C[Finally: resume writers and clean normal staging]

    P1 --> P2
    P2 -->|No| F
    P2 -->|Yes| P3
    P3 --> P4
    P3 --> P5
    P3 --> P6
    P4 --> P7
    P5 --> P7
    P6 --> P7
    P7 -->|No| F
    P7 -->|Yes| P8 --> P8B
    P8B -->|No| F
    P8B -->|Yes| P9
    P9 -->|Absent| P10 --> P12
    P9 -->|Same immutable content| P11 --> P12
    P9 -->|Collision with different content| F
    P12 --> P13
    P13 -->|No| F
    P13 -->|Yes| P14 --> P15
    F --> C
    P15 --> C
  end

  Operator --> P1
  Local --> P4
  Local --> P5
  Local --> P6
  P10 --> Release[(Immutable release artifacts)]
  P11 --> Release
  P12 --> Release
  P14 --> Pointer[(bootstrap/corpus-release.json<br/>current pointer)]

  P3 -. SIGINT or SIGTERM .-> S[Signal guard best-effort resumes writers]
  S --> SX[Process exits with pointer unchanged;<br/>signal-time staging cleanup is not guaranteed]

  subgraph Notes[Implemented scope and limitations]
    N1[Dry-run is read-only: no writer stop, snapshot, staging, cloud call or pointer change]
    N2[Release excludes source code, Docker images/containers, secrets, credentials, auth tokens, logs and cache]
    N3[Local pointer changes only after immutable artifacts and manifest pass read-back verification]
    N4[Cross-store publish/restore uses verification and compensating recovery;<br/>it is not one distributed atomic transaction]
  end
